The paper is about a new software framework for fast training of generalized linear models, which is a topic related to machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The framework also involves recent advances in machine learning systems and algorithms, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The hierarchical architecture of modern computing systems is also mentioned, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The framework is designed for distributed environments, which could be related to cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the framework on a large dataset, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
